<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910402-0023</DOCNO><DOCID>910402-0023.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- Alamco Inc.:   Oil Producer Settles Claims   Brought by Certain Investors</HL><DATE>04/02/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B4</SO><CO>   AXO</CO><MS>ENERGY (ENE)</MS><IN>PETROLEUM (PET)PIPELINE OPERATORS (PIP)</IN><RE>WEST VIRGINIA (WV)</RE><LP>   Alamco Inc., Clarksburg, W.Va., said it settled allmaterial litigation claims brought against it by investors incompany-sponsored drilling programs of the early tomid-1980s.   The company also completed arrangements with Bank One,Texas N.A., a subsidiary of Banc One Corp., for amarket-based $11 million revolving commercial creditfacility.</LP><TEXT>   The company immediately drew on the facility to pay offthe $4.3 million balance on its term note obligation toanother lender.   The producer of gas and oil said it expects to use therest of the Bank One facility for property acquisitions andto step up development of gas and oil properties. The BankOne agreement calls for a two-year commitment period duringwhich Alamco will be responsible for the payment of interestonly on debt balances. The debt balance at the end of thecommitment period is to be amortized in 36 equal payments.   The settlement of the litigation matters marked theelimination of all material financial uncertainties of pastyears.</TEXT></DOC>